Fortress Besieged is a novel by Chinese author Ailing Zhang, first published in 1947. The book has been considered one of the most important works of modern Chinese literature, and it has been translated into many languages.

The story follows Fang Hongjian, a young man who moves from a rural village to Beijing to study at a university. There, he falls in love with the beautiful and intelligent Sun Roujia, but their relationship is complicated by the cultural and societal norms of the time, as well as by the interference of others.